<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>${project_name} Distribution Notes</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #0b1020;
      --panel: rgba(10, 16, 32, 0.88);
      --panel-alt: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.78);
      --line: rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.22);
      --text: #e5edf7;
      --muted: #9db0ca;
      --accent: #4ade80;
      --accent-2: #38bdf8;
      --accent-3: #a78bfa;
      --accent-4: #f59e0b;
      --shadow: 0 24px 60px rgba(2, 6, 23, 0.45);
    }

    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    html {
      scroll-behavior: smooth;
    }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      min-height: 100vh;
      font-family: "Segoe UI Variable Display", "Aptos", "Trebuchet MS", sans-serif;
      color: var(--text);
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.18), transparent 28%),
        radial-gradient(circle at top right, rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.12), transparent 24%),
        linear-gradient(160deg, #060913 0%, #0b1020 48%, #121a30 100%);
    }

    main {
      width: min(1040px, calc(100% - 32px));
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 40px 0 56px;
    }

    .hero,
    .section {
      background: var(--panel);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 24px;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
      backdrop-filter: blur(14px);
    }

    .hero {
      padding: 36px;
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .hero::after {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      inset: auto -120px -120px auto;
      width: 280px;
      height: 280px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.24), rgba(245, 158, 11, 0));
      pointer-events: none;
    }

    .eyebrow {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 10px;
      padding: 8px 14px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.12);
      border: 1px solid rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.2);
      color: var(--accent-2);
      font-size: 0.82rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    h1 {
      margin: 18px 0 8px;
      font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 4.2rem);
      line-height: 0.95;
    }

    .tagline {
      margin: 0 0 14px;
      color: #f8fafc;
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    .subtitle,
    .lead,
    li,
    .card p,
    .footer {
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.72;
    }

    .subtitle {
      max-width: 780px;
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 1.06rem;
    }

    .buttons {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 12px;
      margin-top: 28px;
    }

    .button {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      min-width: 170px;
      padding: 12px 18px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.02em;
      transition: transform 140ms ease, box-shadow 140ms ease, border-color 140ms ease;
    }

    .button:hover {
      transform: translateY(-1px);
    }

    .button-primary {
      color: #07111f;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent), #86efac);
      box-shadow: 0 12px 28px rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.18);
    }

    .button-secondary {
      color: var(--text);
      background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.72);
      border: 1px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.24);
    }

    .stats,
    .feature-grid,
    .doc-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
      gap: 16px;
    }

    .stats {
      margin-top: 22px;
    }

    .section {
      margin-top: 22px;
      padding: 28px 30px;
    }

    .section-header {
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    h2 {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--accent-4);
    }

    h3 {
      margin: 0 0 10px;
      color: #f8fafc;
      font-size: 1.02rem;
    }

    .lead {
      margin: 10px 0 0;
      max-width: 820px;
    }

    .card,
    .feature-group,
    .doc-column {
      padding: 18px;
      border-radius: 18px;
      background: var(--panel-alt);
      border: 1px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.16);
    }

    .card strong,
    .feature-group strong,
    .doc-column strong {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      color: #f8fafc;
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    ol,
    ul {
      margin: 14px 0 0;
      padding-left: 22px;
    }

    .feature-grid,
    .doc-grid {
      margin-top: 18px;
    }

    .doc-column ul,
    .feature-group ul {
      margin-top: 10px;
    }

    a {
      color: var(--accent-2);
    }

    code {
      padding: 0.15rem 0.45rem;
      border-radius: 8px;
      background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.82);
      color: #dbeafe;
      font-family: "Cascadia Code", "Consolas", monospace;
    }

    .footer {
      margin-top: 18px;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      main {
        width: min(100% - 20px, 1040px);
        padding-top: 18px;
      }

      .hero,
      .section {
        border-radius: 18px;
        padding: 24px 20px;
      }

      .button {
        width: 100%;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="eyebrow">${project_name_short} distribution notes</div>
      <h1>${project_name_short}</h1>
      <p class="tagline">Fappin' and Fraggin'</p>
      <p class="subtitle">
        <strong>${project_name_short}</strong> keeps retail <em>Quake III Arena</em> at the center while making the engine feel more at home on modern systems.
      </p>
      <div class="buttons">
        <a class="button button-primary" href="https://github.com/themuffinator/FnQ3/releases/latest">Latest release</a>
        <a class="button button-secondary" href="#getting-started">Getting started</a>
        <a class="button button-secondary" href="#documentation">Documentation</a>
        <a class="button button-secondary" href="#credits">Credits</a>
      </div>
      <div class="stats">
        <article class="card">
          <strong>Compatibility target</strong>
          <p>${compatibility_target}</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <strong>Base version</strong>
          <p>${base_version}</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <strong>Current build</strong>
          <p>${version}</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <strong>Tagged release format</strong>
          <p><code>${release_tag_example}</code></p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="introduction">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p class="lead"><strong>${project_name_short}</strong> is a modernized Quake III Arena source port for players who want the original game to stay recognizably Quake III while gaining cleaner presentation, smoother usability, and better support for current platforms.</p>
      </div>
      <p class="lead">What sets ${project_name_short} apart is restraint: it aims to keep retail compatibility, demos, classic assets, and mod expectations intact first, then layers modern audio, presentation, and quality-of-life improvements on top without changing the identity of the game.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="features">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>2. Features</h2>
        <p class="lead">The headline features are grouped around the same idea: preserve the original game, but make living with it on a modern machine much nicer.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-grid">
        <article class="feature-group">
          <h3>Play the original game with a cleaner modern fit</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Retail Quake III Arena compatibility stays the priority, including classic data, demo playback, and mod expectations.</li>
            <li>SDL3-based video, audio, and input support keeps the engine comfortable on current platforms.</li>
            <li>OpenAL is the default audio path, with improved spatial sound and a safe fallback to the classic mixer.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
        <article class="feature-group">
          <h3>Sharper presentation without losing Quake III's look</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Flexible display controls for renderer choice, fullscreen and windowed play, render scaling, texture picmip filtering, HDR, anti-aliasing, bloom, and cel-shaded world/model presentation.</li>
            <li>Optional extras such as player rim lighting, stencil-style highlights, model cel lighting, and BSP world depth-edge outlines.</li>
            <li>Better widescreen handling for HUDs, menus, UI previews, and cinematics.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
        <article class="feature-group">
          <h3>Better day-to-day usability</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>An upgraded console with smoother scrolling, scaling options, mouse support, text selection, drag and drop, and live completion help.</li>
            <li>Expanded screenshot tools with cleaner naming, optional metadata sidecars, watermark support, and cube-map capture.</li>
            <li>Player-facing quality-of-life touches such as live rainbow text preview and more flexible configuration.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
        <article class="feature-group">
          <h3>Wider content compatibility</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Support for older Quake 3 IHV / q3test maps and legacy <code>.dm3</code> demos alongside standard retail content.</li>
            <li>Practical compatibility for selected Quake Live assets such as <code>IBSP v47</code> maps and encrypted beta <code>.pk3</code> archives.</li>
            <li>Support for Quake II <code>.pak</code> archives and <code>.wal</code> textures for broader content experimentation.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="getting-started">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>3. Getting Started</h2>
        <p class="lead">${project_name_short} is meant to be straightforward for players: keep your original game data, drop in a new executable, and start playing.</p>
      </div>
      <ol>
        <li>Install <em>Quake III Arena</em> and make sure your original <code>baseq3</code> data is present.</li>
        <li>Download the current build from the <a href="https://github.com/themuffinator/FnQ3/releases/latest">latest release page</a>.</li>
        <li>Extract the release archive into your Quake III Arena folder so the FnQuake3 executables sit next to your existing game files.</li>
        <li>Launch the FnQuake3 executable for your platform.</li>
        <li>Use the guides below if you want to tune visuals, audio, screenshots, or console behavior.</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="footer">If you want to build FnQuake3 yourself, use the <a href="https://github.com/themuffinator/FnQ3/blob/main/BUILD.md">Build Guide</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="documentation">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>4. Documentation</h2>
        <p class="lead">The main guides are split between player-facing setup and usage documents, and the deeper build or maintainer references.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="doc-grid">
        <article class="doc-column">
          <h3>Player guides</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="https://github.com/themuffinator/FnQ3/blob/main/docs/DISPLAY.md">Display Guide</a> for renderer choice, video modes, render scaling, texture picmip, HDR, anti-aliasing, bloom, and cel shading.</li>
            <li><a href="https://github.com/themuffinator/FnQ3/blob/main/docs/VISUALS.md">Visuals Guide</a> for player highlighting and other presentation controls.</li>
            <li><a href="https://github.com/themuffinator/FnQ3/blob/main/docs/ASPECT_CORRECTION.md">Aspect Correction Guide</a> for HUD, menu, and cinematic layout options.</li>
            <li><a href="https://github.com/themuffinator/FnQ3/blob/main/docs/AUDIO.md">Audio Guide</a> for backend selection, devices, HRTF, fallback behavior, and troubleshooting.</li>
            <li><a href="https://github.com/themuffinator/FnQ3/blob/main/docs/CONSOLE.md">Console Guide</a> for console layout, scaling, completion, and interaction.</li>
            <li><a href="https://github.com/themuffinator/FnQ3/blob/main/docs/SCREENSHOTS.md">Screenshot Guide</a> for capture commands, naming, metadata sidecars, watermarks, and cube-map export.</li>
            <li><a href="https://github.com/themuffinator/FnQ3/blob/main/docs/fnquake3/CHANGELOG.md">Changelog</a> for release-facing change history.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
        <article class="doc-column">
          <h3>Technical and build docs</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="https://github.com/themuffinator/FnQ3/blob/main/BUILD.md">Build Guide</a> for compiling FnQuake3 locally.</li>
            <li><a href="https://github.com/themuffinator/FnQ3/blob/main/docs/GLX.md">GLx Renderer Guide</a> for the canonical OpenGL-lineage renderer, migration notes, and troubleshooting.</li>
            <li><a href="https://github.com/themuffinator/FnQ3/blob/main/docs/fnquake3/AUDIO_ENGINE.md">Modern Audio Engine Notes</a> for engine architecture and compatibility boundaries.</li>
            <li><a href="https://github.com/themuffinator/FnQ3/blob/main/docs/fnquake3/TECHNICAL.md">Technical Notes</a> for repository structure, release flow, and maintainer conventions.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="credits">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>5. Credits</h2>
        <p class="lead">FnQuake3 follows a clear upstream lineage from the Quake III Arena SDK, through ioquake3, to Quake3e, and then onward through the project-specific work in this repository.</p>
      </div>
      <p class="lead">Additional compatibility and feature work draws from projects and references such as <a href="https://bitbucket.org/CPMADevs/cnq3">CNQ3</a>, <a href="https://github.com/zturtleman/spearmint">Spearmint</a>, <a href="https://github.com/brugal/wolfcamql">WolfcamQL</a>, Luigi Auriemma's <a href="https://aluigi.altervista.org/papers.htm#qldec">qldec</a>, and <a href="https://github.com/Paril/DarkMatter-Q2">DarkMatter-Q2</a>.</p>
      <p class="footer">See the full upstream chain and acknowledgements in <a href="https://github.com/themuffinator/FnQ3/blob/main/CREDITS.md">CREDITS.md</a>.</p>
    </section>
  </main>
</body>
</html>
